{"id":"301916727_Local_linear_double_and_asymmetric_kernel_estimation_of_conditional_quantiles","abstract":"In this work, we propose and investigate a family of non parametric quantile regression estimates. The proposed estimates combine local linear fitting and double kernel approaches. More precisely, we use a Beta kernel when covariateâ€™s support is compact and Gamma kernel for left-bounded supports. Finite sample properties together with asymptotic behavior of the proposed estimators are presented. It is also shown that these estimates enjoy the property of having finite variance and resistance to sparse design.","authors":["M.-Anas Knefati","Abder Oulidi","Belkacem Abdous"],"meta":["June 2016Communication in Statistics- Theory and Methods 45(12):3473-3488","DOI:10.1080/03610926.2014.889923"],"references":["241715427_Design-adaptive_nonparametric_estimation_of_conditional_quantile_derivatives","38359753_Local_Linear_Regression_Smoothers_and_Their_Minimax_Efficiencies","30526485_Estimation_of_Conditional_Densities_and_Sensitivity_Measures_in_Nonlinear_Dynamical_Systems","24052384_Local_Polynomial_Regression_Optimal_Kernels_and_Asymptotic_Minimax_Efficiency","321594764_Nonlinear_Time_Series_Nonparametric_and_Parametric_Methods","288420770_Cross-validation_in_nonparametric_quantile_regression","275841721_Local_Polynomial_Modeling_and_Its_Applications","271512995_Nonlinear_Time_Series","268617586_Robust_nonparametric_function_estimation","246709391_Local_Linear_Quantile_Regression","239994015_Finite-Sample_Variance_of_Local_Polynomials_Analysis_and_Solutions","233801137_Regression_Quantile","228546078_Beta_kernel_smoothers_for_regression_curves","222632152_Non-parametric_estimation_of_conditional_quantiles","222502181_Beta_Kernel_estimators_for_density_functions","24052647_Local_Linear_Smoothers_Using_Asymmetric_Kernels","24052546_Probability_Density_Function_Estimation_Using_Gamma_Kernels","23775653_Nonparametric_estimation_of_conditional_VaR_and_expected_shortfal